President Donald Trump has sent a notice to Congress stating that the national emergency with respect to the situation in Burundi, which was declared in Executive Order 13712 in November 2015, is to continue in effect beyond November 22, 2019. The situation in Burundi has been characterized by violence against civilians, unrest, incitement of violence, and political repression, posing a threat to the peace, security, and stability of Burundi and the region. Therefore, President Trump has determined that it is necessary to continue the national emergency.